Timely Team Scheduling Application

The scheduling application is an Java FX desktop application that allows a user to manage appointments for
a consulting business that conducts business in multiple languages and office locations in various regions
of the world.

Appointments, contacts and customers can be created, updated or deleted via the application and stored in
MySQL database. Reports can be viewed that shows appointments by contact, appointments by country and the total count
of each type of appointment.

Author: Lachelle Allen
Contact information: lall319@wgu.edu
Application version: 1.0
Date: 12/29/2022

IDE: IntelliJ IDEA 2021.1.3 (Community Edition)
Java Version 17.0.1 2021-10-19 LTS
JavaFX Scene Builder 17.0.0

Directions:
Import project into IntelliJ IDEA.
Run from main.
A login in screen will appear first, username is admin, password is admin.

Reports:
A 3rd report was added to allow the user to view appointments by country. Viewing appointments by country
will help the company with market analysis, track how well they are doing, allocate resources and plan for
possible expansion or locate promising markets.
This report uses a SQL query that joins multiple tables including appointments, first level divisions, customers
and countries to filter and select the appointments by countries currently supported by the company.

MySQL Connector Driver Version: mysql-connector-java-8.0.25

Lambda #1 is found at NewCustomerController.countryComboBoxAction()
Lambda #2 is found at ReportsByMonthController.initialize